snippet.textDisplay:
The problem with these news outlets is that their word choice is designed to invoke panic, here are a few examples why this is blown way more than it should be:
1) they are using percentages for Trip Cancellations and Travel Insurance which could mean that it jumped from 100,000 to 121,000k (that isn't that much) so a percent increase here sounds much more alarming.
2) they are out here complaining about many people running drugstores out of masks however their news reporter in a highly contagious region isn't wearing one which shows that the panic is much less than what they are imposing.
3) If you watch or ask any doctor (Dr.Mike is a good example here on YouTube) that keeps track of the spread of the disease will tell you to be more "Alert" than "Anxious" as being anxious will only cause problems such as mass paranoia and hysteria which only leads to greater issues. Also, the mortality rate is overly exaggerated as most patients diagnosed only demonstrate mild symptoms and usually move on with their lives afterwards. The fear here is that it might infect those with already compromised immune systems hence the only terrifying aspect is its infectivity rate.
Overall, remember to stay alert and remain calm.

*source: Basic statistically probability from an Elementary Probablity and Statistcs course/ also in the pre-med pathway.
